    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20/171</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-12">September 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Iranian Minister called at his request and emphasized his request heretofore
                    made in behalf of his Government for a military mission from this country to
                    come to Iran, including a qualified expert in transportation and an outstanding
                    businessman. He said that the work of all these types of Americans would be a
                    fine thing for the United Nations cause, especially for closer relations between
                    our two countries. I expressed keen interest in all phases of this suggestion
                    and assured the Minister that I would give the matter sympathetic attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
